description.plain:
Magnus August Høiberg (born November 29, 1987), best known under the artist name Cashmere Cat, is a Norwegian musician, producer, DJ and turntablist (representing Norway in the DMC World DJ Championships as DJ FINAL 2006–09).

He appeared on the international electronic dance music scene in 2012, with remixes and edits of songs by Lana Del Rey, 2 Chainz, and Jeremih. At first, he used to go by the moniker “KATTEN”, which is Norwegian for “the cat”. However, he changed his name to Cashmere Cat to make it more understandable for people worldwide.

His debut EP, “Mirror Maru”, released in October 2012, gained recognition from several other producers. His all-star debut studio album “9” was released on April 28, 2017. His sophomore album “Princess Catgirl” was released on September 20, 2019.

songs.title: Quit

description.plain:
“Quit” is the third collaboration between Norwegian producer Cashmere Cat and songstress Ariana Grande. The first collaboration appeared on Grande’s My Everything in the track “Be My Baby” and later on collaborated on the song “Adore.”

Lyrically the song is about a love struck Ariana but all her friends and people around her telling her not to fall in love with them, but she can’t resist. The song has similar themes to Grande’s 2016 summer hit, “Side to Side” featuring Nicki Minaj.

Cashmere Cat debuted “Quit” during one of his sets in Pittsburgh, PA on April 25, 2017. Sia’s demo of the song leaked in early 2017 some fans speculating it would appear on  her next project

Grande performed the song by herself for the first time at the first show of the European leg of her Dangerous Woman Tour on May 08, 2017 in Stockholm, Sweden.

songs.title: Trust Nobody
songs.title_with_featured: Trust Nobody (Ft. Selena Gomez & Tory Lanez)

description.plain:
“Trust Nobody” is about keeping a sexual relationship lowkey. Tory, Selena, and Cashmere Cat are all pretty big stars, and if it was discovered any of them were dating or hooking up with someone, it would likely be publicized to a point where it would stress the relationship. As a result of this, none of them trust anyone to keep a relationship secret.

The song is the second single off Cashmere Cat’s upcoming debut album 9. It arrives after the lead single, “Wild Love” that featured The Weeknd and Francis and the Lights.

songs.full_title: Adore by Cashmere Cat (Ft. Ariana Grande)
songs.title: Adore

description.plain:
As Cashmere Cat, Norwegian producer Magnus August Høiberg officially released lead single Adore on March 3 2015. It appears on his forthcoming debut album, which will follow 2014 EP Wedding Bells.

Adore was debuted live on February 25 2015, during Cashmere Cat’s support DJ set on the first leg of Ariana Grande’s Honeymoon tour. It features Grande’s silky R&B-inspired vocals over a synth-heavy beat, and focuses primarily on love in its giddy, newfound stage.
